5","parent":"222","text":"VPPB → causa más frecuente vértigo en AM","guid":"","children":[{"id":"236","parent":"235","text":"Maniobra Dix-Hallpike diagnóstica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"237","parent":"235","text":"Maniobra Epley terapéutica → resolución >80%","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"238","parent":"0","text":"PERLAS CLÍNICAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"239","parent":"238","text":"Diabético añoso con otorrea refractaria + granulación CAE = OTITIS MALIGNA → hospitalizar + cipro EV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"240","parent":"238","text":"Vesículas CAE + sordera/vértigo/parálisis facial = RAMSAY HUNT → aciclovir EV URGENTE","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"241","parent":"238","text":"ACHIEVE trial: audífonos reducen 48% deterioro cognitivo 3a SOLO en pacientes de RIESGO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"242","parent":"238","text":"Cohorte de novo (voluntarios sanos) SIN efecto → tasa declive 3x más lenta, no detectable en 3a","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"243","parent":"238","text":"Screening hipoacusia desde 50 años en TODO encuentro clínico (AAO-HNSF 2024)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"244","parent":"238","text":"Hipoacusia en AM → SIEMPRE evaluar función vestibular (correlación anatómica cóclea-vestíbulo)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"245","parent":"238","text":"Implante coclear SEGURO >80a → anestesia local + sedación consciente factible","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"246","parent":"238","text":"Audífonos mejoran equilibrio postural → doble beneficio: audición + prevención caídas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"247","parent":"238","text":"Presbiacusia tipo estrial/metabólica = MEJOR respuesta a audífonos (audiometría plana, discriminación ok)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"248","parent":"238","text":"Otomicosis: NUNCA antimicóticos orales → solo tópicos + curaciones microscópicas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"249","parent":"238","text":"Cerumen en AM = más seco y duro → causa tratable de hipoacusia, siempre descartar antes de audiometría","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"250","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"251","parent":"250","text":"1. Brocklehurst's Textbook of Geriatric Medicine. Cap 12: Otolaryngology in Older Adults. 9th ed. 2023.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"252","parent":"250","text":"2. Tsai Do BS et al. Clinical Practice Guideline: Age-Related Hearing Loss. Otolaryngol Head Neck Surg. 2024;170(S2):S1-S54.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"253","parent":"250","text":"3. Lin FR et al. Hearing intervention versus health education control (ACHIEVE trial). Lancet. 2023;402(10404):786-797.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"254","parent":"250","text":"4. Azevedo C et al. Vestibular and cochlear dysfunction in aging. World J Otorhinolaryngol Head Neck Surg. 2022;8(4):308-314.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"255","parent":"250","text":"5. Jilla AM et al. A Geriatrician's Guide to Hearing Loss. J Am Geriatr Soc. 2021;69(5):1190-1198.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"256","parent":"250","text":"6. Sharma RK et al. Modeling Hearing Loss Progression in the Older Old. Laryngoscope. 2021;131(4):879-884.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"257","parent":"250","text":"7. Denham MW et al. Hearing Loss and Reduced Income Growth. Otolaryngol Head Neck Surg. 2024;171(3):740-746.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"258","parent":"250","text":"8. Dr. Matamala. Clase Oído Externo. Universidad Mayor. 2015.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"259","parent":"250","text":"9. Livingston G et al. Dementia prevention, intervention, and care. Lancet Commission. 2020;396(10248):413-446.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":259,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"Modulo2 Oido Envejece iPad","id":"map_820","resolved_references":[]}